{"body": {"name": "Reza DevRel Contributor Report 2024-08-27 - 2024-09-17", "summary": "Following an initial alignment with @gagdiez.near, and as the winner of the AI track on EthGlobal Brussels, I am looking forward to contribute to the AI docs as well as AI derived tooling such as the near-py package.", "category": "Decentralized DevRel", "timeline": {"status": "REVIEW", "sponsor_requested_review": false, "reviewer_completed_attestation": false}, "supervisor": "gagdiez.near", "description": "## Timeline\\\\nStart Date: August 27, 2024\\\\nEnd Date: September 17, 2024\\\\n\\\\n## Requested Funding\\\\nHours: 5:35\\\\nRate: $50/hour\\\\nTotal Amount: $279\\\\n\\\\n## Summary of Activities\\\\n#### Contributions\\\\n15min - Fix dependency issues in py-near with latest version of Python https://github.com/pvolnov/py-near/pull/24\\\\n2h30 - Designing a base architecture for an AI assistant on Near docs by learning about similar projects and ideas, looking at the structure of the documents and respecting the constraint of the project (no embedding vectors to simply summarize the content, which can lead to hallucinations, but simply having a search in natural language with results given as links to relevant parts of the documentation)\\\\n1h30 - Starting to implement categorizations of selected documents (which ended up behing too unreliable for our use case) and exploring integrations with Algolia (to instead plug our AI feature in the existing search component, or a custom version of it)\\\\n\\\\n#### General / Other\\\\n1h20 - One-on-One with Guillermo (27/08, 04/09, 17/09)", "linked_proposals": [181], "receiver_account": "rezarah.near", "requested_sponsor": "neardevdao.near", "proposal_body_version": "V0", "requested_sponsorship_usd_amount": "279", "requested_sponsorship_paid_in_currency": "USDC"}, "labels": [], "accepted_terms_and_conditions_version": 128260196}
